name: ELLSWORTH HILL ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: The Hudson City Schools Integrated Preschool Program is an early intervention program for children with disabilities and typically developing children between the ages of 3-5 years.  Children are identified as having special needs through a multi-factored evaluation which consists of a play-based assessment performed by the school team (school psychologist, special education teacher, speech pathologist, occupational therapist and/or physical therapist).  Children with disabilities in our program have a wide range of needs including communication, hearing, motor (fine and/or gross), vision, cognition, adaptive behavior (self-help skills), and/or social/emotional/behavioral functioning.  Peer models are selected through a screening process which identifies peers who demonstrate typical skills in all areas and strong skills in the areas of social and communication.  The program offers a 'hands-on' teaching approach to promote academic, social, communicative, behavioral and motoric growth and development.  Our curriculum is based on the Ohio Department of Education's Early Learning and Development Standards.

Students will be asked to design solutions to real-world problems that are relevant to them. This form of instruction is both engaging and exciting for students. They are learning by doing. I invite you to partner with the school in open, honest and continuous communication concerning your child to ensure a successful home-school partnership.

In our Christ-centered curriculum, God's word is the standard of truth and authority by which all subjects are taught.

name: GRACE WESLEYAN CH-HEAVEN'S TREASURE

It is supported and enriched by technology in all aspects of teaching and learning, as implemented at TGS and TCS. GEMS is also committed to its partnership with EL Education and its three dimensions of student achievement: Mastery of knowledge and skills, character, and high-quality student work. We address the important learning arc that provides the transition from elementary school to success in middle school, and on to success in high school, not only academically but in terms of character development and understanding of the communities in which students live.

Goals within our curriculum reflect the philosophy of serving children according to their needs and to educate children who have been identified special needs in a setting that includes typically developing peers. These interactions provide benefit for all children in the areas of social interaction, modeling and developmental progress.

name: GREAT WESTERN LEARNING CENTER, LLC. DBA HAPPY DAYS D

name: IMMANUEL LUTHERAN
details: Preschool Age Children will: Learn ABC's, numbers, shapes, colors, the calendar and the pledges to the American and Christian flags. Have free play with toys, puzzles and games with peers. Do group arts and crafts, sing and dance, play learning and computer games and even learn some sign language. Hear stories from the Bible and children's books. Eat Breakfast, lunch and snack. (Breakfast and snack are provided) Have special themes in the summer with field trips and extra activities.

name: INCARNATE WORD ACADEMY
details: Incarnate Word Academy is the sponsored ministry of the Sisters of the Incarnate Word. As a community of learners filled with the Spirit of the Word-Made-Flesh, we are committed to living Gospel values and inspiring academic excellence.

name: INCARNATION
details: At Incarnation, we understand that selecting the right school for your child involves a thoughtful decision. The early years of a child’s education are among the most influential, not just for building foundation for academic excellence, but for developing character, values, and beliefs. Incarnation Catholic School partners with parents to enhance knowledge, understanding, and celebrate what it means to be a child of God.

name: INDEPENDENCE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Independence is one of six elementary schools within the Lima City Schools. Independence services K-4 students.

name: INDEPENDENCE PRIMARY SCHOOL
details: The primary objective of the Independence Board of Education is to provide all of the students of this community with an education consistent with state standards, as well as community educational expectations. The home and the school must work cooperatively for the benefit of the students’ continuous growth and development. Students shall be accepted, treated, and respected as unique human beings. Students will be encouraged to develop their intellectual faculties in preparation for contributing roles in our democratic society.

name: INDIAN HILL PRIMARY SCHOOL
details: When your children excitedly enter the Indian Hill Primary School doors for their first day of kindergarten, they are not thinking about what they'll need for a successful high school career. But we are, from the moment they arrive.

name: INDIAN RIFFLE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Indian Riffle is known for its strong commitment to academic excellence, hard working students and supportive parents.  Our goal is to create a learning environment that is safe, academically focused and challenging.  We hope to build a strong, working school-parent-community relationship that will enhance the learning experience of our students and be a warm, inviting place for our parents and the community.

name: INDIAN SPRINGS ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Columbus City Schools has high-quality schools and programs to meet every child’s needs. Whether you’re interested in traditional schools, or alternative schools featuring performing arts, STEM, language immersion, gender-specific, or career-technical programming, you’ll find top-notch schools that will help your child to learn, dream, and succeed.

name: INDIAN TRAIL SCHOOL
details: The Indian Trail School Community is committed to educating all students in becoming successful citizens in a global society by providing academic rigor and 21st Century skills in a positive and caring learning environment.

name: INDIANOLA INFORMAL K-8 SCHOOL
details: Columbus City Schools has high-quality schools and programs to meet every child’s needs. Whether you’re interested in traditional schools, or alternative schools featuring performing arts, STEM, language immersion, gender-specific, or career-technical programming, you’ll find top-notch schools that will help your child to learn, dream, and succeed.

name: INSPIRE CENTER FOR LEARNING
details: From the moment your children walk through the door at Inspire Center for Learning, they are excited and inspired to learn. Inspire presents an environment that breaks down the boundaries of traditional daycare and opens up the possibilities to a new and exciting way to view your child’s development.

name: INTERNATIONAL ACADEMY OF CINCINNATI, INC.
details: The Academy is truly a special place, where our mission is to educate students in an Islamic setting is unique to the tri-state area. We have a highly qualified staff who cares about the success of each and every student; and who through their years of service and dedication, have formed and supported the strong foundation of excellence in education in our school. As a private charter school, we have developed strong ties with the local community.

name: IOWA-MAPLE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Iowa-Maple is an elementary school (PreK-8) in the Glenville area where engaging teachers and building leaders work cooperatively to grow their scholars. Improving core academic skills is our priority, but fostering a culture where scholars can grow socially, emotionally, and behaviorally is our passion and leads to well-rounded young men and women.

name: J F BURNS ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: We are committed to quality and habits necessary for future success.

name: J F KENNEDY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: From our outstanding academic offerings, to strong, award-winning performing and fine arts programs, to a wide variety of student clubs, to the full line-up of athletic opportunities available to our students, the Kettering City Schools are places where there is “something for everyone!” We are proud to represent a community that is focused on quality of education for all students and quality of life for all who live here.

name: J T KARAFFA ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: Success for All makes reading the cornerstone of the curriculum.

name: J W REASON ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
details: JW Reason Elementary School is one of 14 elementary schools in the Hilliard City School District.

name: J.F. DULLES ELEMENTARY
details: Our work continues at JF Dulles Elementary School to build students with strong character, academic excellence and exemplary citizenship! To enhance all that we do to ensure a positive learning environment, the JFD community embraces Positive Behavior Support Intervention Systems
